			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">We definitely should not allow int3 on x86-32, because Mac OS X has a bug which prevents int3 from delivering an exception to the exception handler when the %cs segment has a non-zero base.  See https://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2879#c6.  We went to some trouble to work around this in the debug stub and use hlt for breakpoints instead.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-01-21T02:22:20.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2013-01-21T02:22:20.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 14 by mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=645#c14" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/645/comments/full/14" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>